===Etymology===
From Japanese [[定石]] (jōseki), literally [[定]] ''set'' + [[石]] ''stone''.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
#(''[[w:Go (board game)|go]]'') A studied and standardized sequence of moves in game of Go in which both players go head-to-head, especially at a corner of the board, in the opening phase of a game.

